      "from": "opencode",
      "type": "instruction",
      "message": "PROJECT CONTEXT:\nParadisio is a static web directory of ~772 businesses within 5km of Puerto Viejo de Talamanca, Costa Rica. Built as a static site on GitHub Pages (Python build.py -> HTML/JSON).\n\nRECENT COMPLETED WORK:\n1. OSM cross-ref: 418 candidates found, 407 CIDs resolved via authenticated Google Maps search\n2. 22 validated new businesses merged into master CSV (750 -> 772)\n3. V2 Maps enrichment: ALL 715 CIDs re-crawled with signed-in Chrome, full text saved per CID (avg 3,594 chars, 2.6M total chars) instead of previous 300-char truncation\n4. Full text corpus preserved in maps_enrich_v2.json\n\nWHAT'S CURRENTLY SURFACED IN THE APP:\n- Rating, address, check-in/out times, amenity chips, prices\n- Subcategory (e.g. \"Hotel\", \"Italian restaurant\")\n- Source badges, contact channels (phone, WhatsApp, Instagram, FB, website)\n- Description from master CSV\n\nWHAT EXISTS IN THE FULL TEXT BUT ISN'T MINED:\n- Open/closed status (297 entries) and operating hours (259) — captured but not displayed\n- Business descriptions / owner blurbs (paragraphs, marketing copy)\n- Competitor names + ratings + prices\n- Vacation rental listings with room/bath counts\n- Peak hours / busy times data\n- Review excerpts (Google + TripAdvisor)\n- Category-specific fields: cuisine type, dietary options, price level, languages, payment methods\n- Photo URLs\n- Structured data (JSON-LD) from the page\n\nCORE QUESTION:\nI need your strategic assessment:\n1. What high-value fields should we extract from the full text next, prioritized by user-facing impact?\n2. What's the best architecture for a re-parse pipeline (category-aware parsers as recommended in the CID v2 methodology)?\n3. Are there any data fields we should consider adding to the platform monetization strategy (premium listings, classifieds, advertising)?\n4. What's missing from our data that we should go get (not from text but from other sources)?\n5. Surface any concerns: data quality, stale data risk, competitive positioning, technical debt.\n\nPlease read the following key files (read paths relative to project root):\n- docs/paradisio_status_and_ideas.md\n- docs/cid_enrichment_strategy_report.md (for category-aware parsing context)\n- paradisio_app/maps_enrich_v2.py (for the parser code)\n- paradisio_app/build.py (for how data flows into the app)\n- docs/cid_v2_extraction_methodology.md (for methodology)\n\nBe thorough, critical, and specific. I want an adversarial/red-team perspective — poke holes in our approach.",
